  "prompt": "How do you pre-select a seat when booking a flight on Royal Air Maroc?",
  "response": "To pre-select a seat when booking a flight with Royal Air Maroc, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Booking Process**: During the flight booking process on the Royal Air Maroc website, you'll typically come to a step that allows you to choose your seats. \n\n2. **Manage Your Booking**: If you\u2019ve already completed your booking, you can manage your reservation through the \"Manage My Booking\" section on the Royal Air Maroc website. You will need your booking reference and last name to log in.\n\n3. **Seat Selection**: Once in your booking details, look for options related to seat selection. You can view the seat map for your flight and choose your preferred seat, if available.\n\n4. **Fees**: Be aware that some seats may come with an additional fee, especially for preferred locations like extra legroom seats.\n\n5. **Mobile App**: You can also use the Royal Air Maroc mobile app to select and change seats if you've already made a booking.\n\n6. **Check-In**: If you haven't selected a seat during the initial booking, you may still have the option to choose a seat during online check-in, which usually opens 24 to 48 hours before departure.\n\n7. **Customer Service**: If you encounter any issues or have specific requests, consider reaching out to Royal Air Maroc customer service for assistance.\n\nAlways check the airline's official website for the most accurate and updated information regarding seat selection, as policies and procedures can change.",
